  "title": "Chemical Plant Operator (East)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Role Overview:</strong></h3>\n<p>Responsible for operating and maintaining chemical processing and support equipment, ensuring smooth production workflows, safety compliance, and quality control in a pilot-scale manufacturing environment.</p>\n<h3><strong>Core Duties:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct material testing using instruments such as TGA analyzers and tensile strength testers.</li>\n  <li>Perform preventive maintenance on mechanical components like pumps, valves, mixers, and tanks.</li>\n  <li>Manage chemical receiving, unloading, and storage in line with standard operating procedures.</li>\n  <li>Support fibre processing and wetlaid operations, including batch documentation and traceability.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Qualifications &amp; Skills:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Higher Nitec/Nitec in Chemical Process Technology, or equivalent certifications (e.g., WSQ in Chemical Operations and WSH).</li>\n  <li>Hands-on experience with lab and plant equipment including mixers, pumps, and valves.</li>\n</ul>",
